Super easy super delicious. I've made these twice now to rave reviews ("restaurant quality"), the key to having them spicy or not - some have stated they are too spicy for them - is how long you let the ribs sit with the rub on them before cooking. If you let the ribs sit overnight in the rub it penetrates more for a spicier rib. If you just let them sit room temp for an hour you will just have a hint of the flavors. Both ways yummy so really just about preference. I use Brooklyn lager for the beer and also use rum as a sub for the some of the water in the sauce with excellent results.

