Rating: 1
I read all of the reviews with great anticipation. These ribs were marginal, at best. I have a recipe I've made for years that's much easier and way better. Just put the slabs in a roasting pan, arranged so they're not stacked on top of one another, but they will overlap. Cover them tightly with foil and bake at 300 degrees for two hours. For the sauce, dice one medium onion and mince 2 or 3 garlic cloves. Saute them in a deep pot with 2 Tbsp butter until clear. Stir in 1 cup of ketchup, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 heaping Tbsp chili powder, 1 teaspoon dried basil, and 1 Tbsp lemon juice. Heat thoroughly, about 10 minutes. Put the ribs on a BBQ grill to finish them, basting with the sauce. The time depends upon the heat of the grill, they will be very tender so they may not need to cook for long. Serve the ribs, passing more of the sauce. This will get RAVE reviews and has much greater flavor and is much less trouble than this recipe. Have fun!

