Actually, the previous reviewer is totally WRONG! Barbecue refers to hot smoking of meat at low temperatures with various rubs, marinades and sauces. Grilling refers to cooking or finishing meats and/or vegetables at higher temperature. This obviously a baked dish finished on the grill. So who cares? I am truly confused about the fuss, as the recipe does not even claim to be barbecue, it is merely finished with barbecue sauce. Bid deal. It looks good to me!

