Rating: 1
These are cheatin' ribs. A proper rib is done on a 200-250 degree grill for 3 hours or more wearing nothing but a dry rub. Purists use a kettle, but my wife gets it "dropping off the bone" on a 3 burner Weber gas grill. Nobody eats ribs with a fork, so fork tender is beside the point. A little sauce thinned with vinegar and brushed on near the end is optional. If I got this in a restaurant and it claimed to be real barbeque, I would send it back.

